                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of ʻAhdnāmah by Different authors
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4562-item1">
                     <author key="person_f4302" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="en" type="desc">Different authors</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9161">ʻAhdnāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_9161">عهدنامه</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true"/>
                     <note>A copy of the Persian text of the Treaty of Commerce negotiated between the <name type="org" key="n79118917">East India Company</name> and the <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f3137" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">Nauwāb Āṣaf al-Daulah of Oudh, <foreign xml:lang="fa">آصف الدوله</foreign>
                        </persName>, and signed by <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20760091" key="viaf_20760091" type="standard" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">Lord Cornwallis</persName>, Governor-General, on behalf of the Company, and by the Nawab-Wazir for himself, on <date calendar="Gregorian" when="1788">15th July, 1788</date>.See <ref target="Aitchison_1893" type="page">Aitchison 1893, page 15.</ref>
                     </note>
                     <note>The text of the treaty was printed at <name type="place" key="subject_n80049617">Calcutta</name> in <date calendar="Gregorian" when="1788">1788</date>, in English, Persian, and Bengali: this pamphlet, one of the incunabula of Persian and Bengali printing, is now exceedingly rare, but a copy is preserved in the India Office ibrary
                     </note>
                     <note>A note on the fly-leaf, in a hand dated 1828, reads: </note>
                     <quote xml:lang="en">"Written for his Highness's own use."</quote>
                     <note/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Arberry 1939, pages 355-6.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
